Pretty little garden with trees, it has play areas for children. The name of this square pays homage to the writer Jules Verne (1828-1905). It hosts a local facility, the Pavilion Ã  la ClÃ©, and a shared garden, where educational activities are set up in the form of practical workshops in the fields of ecology and gardening.
Nice park anchored on a charming site, with a greenhouse to visit. Ideal for taking the children out.
Small, friendly and unpretentious square near Belleville, with a play area for children

During school holidays, maintenance of the sandbox is completely forgotten (see photo of dog droppings for three weeks). Since the start of the school year, the sandbox has unfortunately been cleaned from time to time. Maintaining the rope breaks from time to time but each time it is repaired.  On the other hand, the holes on the ground in the tarmac are still present. And the big turnstile has been broken for a long time but still not repaired. The small turnstile has been repaired. Very often on weekends in any case the park is still not open at 9:15 a.m.... 15 minutes of waiting in the cold and a complaining child.
Nice place for children and parents Too bad as often that this place is not well maintained, especially with regard to cleanliness.

This park clearly deserves to redo the paths which are irregular and dangerous for children. Other than that, some nice games and a fairly clean sandbox. At the bottom, small and pretty shared gardens. Very lively.

One of the nicest children's parks around Parmentier. Well maintained, a nice mix of children. A small sandbox and a participatory garden. Certain days the small participatory library brings out the deckchairs and cushions so that young and old can read in the sun. Not very big so a lot of people leaving school.

Very well secured and lots of games for children from 2 to 10 years old in summer, film screenings, sometimes the library for children. Very good overall, except for the toilets which need to be taken care of over time, the rest is impeccable. In addition it is well maintained outside thank you

Very large and pleasant, there is room for adults and children and very small children. Activities are often organized there for the public, it's cool, there are enough games to keep the children busy.

The Paris town hall is letting the square deteriorate visibly! To renovate quickly!  Large square, little shade, many games for children. Unfortunately the ground is deteriorating rapidly now and the games lack maintenance.

Nice place for children with a media library which plays songs or contines for children during this period. Further down, a shared garden unfortunately ransacked and pillaged by people with bad intentions! Small downside for the very present pigeons which dirty tables and benches...
Small park from our childhood, still so clean and ideal for lunch breaks ðŸ˜œ â€¦

This neighborhood square is great thanks to the neighborhood cooperative garden. The people who take care of it are very kind and welcoming. They allowed us to take a few photos for a bachelorette party. It made a nice setting.

Neighborhood square, certain places should be avoided: between the undocumented immigrants (who come to wash, sleep on the benches, smoke), the drunks, the drug dealers, it nevertheless remains a nerve center for the children of the neighborhood. A good point for the association which offers activities around books in the square, this helps to broaden the audience.
I like it a little because it is small so for small children it is good but from 4:30 p.m. not too many people for a small park
Pleasant park for children of all ages. Secure.
Square with equipment suitable for children. Too bad there are lots of drug dealers squatting on the benches and this in the middle of the day when the square is full of children.
Interesting for children
Children's park with games for the youngest 2/3 years old and for adults from 5 years old. Plus a sandy area, a small mountain with a tunnel for playing with little cars.
A nice little square to take your children
There is a compost, a shared garden, a book box, in addition to children's games. Lively and popular places surrounded by associations.
Pleasant for adults and children.. With separate corners if you come without children.. Cultivated garden corner..
Small square with a slide for little ones. Peaceful and a bit of greenery much appreciated.
If you like parks filled with drugs and zombies this is perfect! too bad, children love games
This garden, which was a great place for families, has become a place for drug dealing, thanks to the migrant shelter located not far away.
The park is good but unfortunately some young men disturb the atmosphere
A clean place loved by children, unfortunately it is cold
Good but lots of squatters and people who smoke in the presence of children.
Neighborhood square... we have fun there.
